The paper deals with a distributed parameter estimation problem in wireless sensor networks, which involves communication and information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and systems and control (cs.SY). The proposed algorithm is based on machine learning techniques (cs.LG) and involves statistical analysis (cs.MA) to evaluate its efficiency through simulation experiments.
